    "source": "https://example.com/classic-lasagne",
    "originalText": "# Classic Lasagne\n\nA proper layered lasagne with slow-cooked meat sauce and silky béchamel. Serves 6.\n\n## Ingredients\n\n### Meat Sauce\n- 1 large onion, finely diced\n- 2 medium carrots, finely diced\n- 2 stalks celery, finely diced\n- 3 cloves garlic, minced\n- 500 g beef mince (80/20)\n- 400 g crushed tomatoes (one 400 g tin)\n- 70 g tomato paste (double concentrate)\n- 120 ml red wine (dry Italian)\n- 15 ml olive oil\n- 5 g salt\n- 2 g black pepper\n- 3 g dried oregano\n\n### Béchamel\n- 60 g butter\n- 60 g plain flour\n- 750 ml whole milk\n- 1 g nutmeg (freshly grated)\n\n### Assembly\n- 250 g dried lasagne sheets (no-boil)\n- 200 g mozzarella, coarsely grated\n- 50 g Parmesan, finely grated\n\n## Equipment\n- Large heavy-bottomed pan or Dutch oven\n- Medium saucepan\n- Whisk\n- 9×13 inch baking dish\n- Oven\n- Cutting board and knife\n- Grater\n\n## Instructions\n\n1. **Prep the soffritto**: Finely dice the onion, carrots, and celery. Mince the garlic.\n2. **Build the base**: Heat olive oil in a large pan over medium heat. Add the diced onion, carrot, and celery. Cook for 8 minutes, stirring occasionally, until softened. Add garlic and cook 1 minute more.\n3. **Brown the meat**: Increase heat to medium-high. Add the beef mince, breaking it up. Cook 6-7 minutes until well browned. Season with salt and pepper.\n4. **Deglaze**: Pour in red wine and scrape up browned bits. Let bubble 2 minutes.\n5. **Build the sauce**: Stir in crushed tomatoes, tomato paste, and oregano. Bring to a gentle simmer.\n6. **Simmer**: Reduce heat to low, cover partially, and simmer for 25 minutes, stirring occasionally.\n7. **Make the béchamel**: While the meat sauce simmers, melt butter in a medium saucepan over medium-low heat. Add flour and whisk constantly for 2-3 minutes until pale golden. Gradually add milk, whisking constantly to prevent lumps. Cook until thickened enough to coat the back of a spoon. Season with nutmeg and a pinch of salt.\n8. **Preheat oven** to 180°C (350°F).\n9. **Grate cheeses**: Coarsely grate the mozzarella. Finely grate the Parmesan.\n10. **Assemble**: Spread a thin layer of meat sauce in the baking dish. Layer lasagne sheets, meat sauce, béchamel, and mozzarella. Repeat for 3-4 layers. Finish with béchamel and remaining mozzarella on top.\n11. **Bake**: Cover with foil and bake 25 minutes. Remove foil and bake 10 more minutes until golden and bubbling.\n12. **Rest**: Let stand 10-15 minutes before cutting — this is essential for clean slices.\n13. **Serve**: Cut into portions and top with freshly grated Parmesan.\n\n## Notes\n\nThe béchamel must be smooth — whisk constantly when adding milk. Resting after baking is essential; the layers set as they cool slightly. Leftovers reheat beautifully at 160°C for 20 minutes covered with foil.",
